<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,469,464,524]" box="[151,427,500,524]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,260,500,524]" captionStart="PLATE 2" captionStartId="23.[151,233,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,199,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-84@23.[151,1436,193,1893]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="PLATE 2. A–H. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Licontinia recurvata, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Licontinia multisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (C) Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Panoldia minuta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Sapingia calcaris, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Stalolidia setacea, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Stalolidia bulbata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Stalolidia flangella, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Plate 2D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[271,419,500,524]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–100" captionStartId="29.[197,310,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,521,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-497@29.[266,1316,510,1951]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 93–100. Panolidia minuta, sp. nov. (93) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (94) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (95) right style, lateral view; (96) right style, dorsal view; (97) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (98) aedeagus, dorsal view; (99) connective, dorsal view; (100) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs. 93–100</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,572,1244]" box="[151,630,572,596]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,572,596]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 6.80 mm., female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,572,1244]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,460,608,632]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Medium sized, slender species. General color concolorous dark brown to black; forewings grayish black except for brown clavus, costal area and apex; mesonotum, pronotum and crown brown; eyes light yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[335,439,679,703]" captionStart="PLATE 2" captionStartId="23.[151,233,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,199,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-84@23.[151,1436,193,1893]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="PLATE 2. A–H. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Licontinia recurvata, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Licontinia multisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (C) Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Panoldia minuta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Sapingia calcaris, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Stalolidia setacea, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Stalolidia bulbata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Stalolidia flangella, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Plate 2D</figureCitation>
); face light yellow. Head nearly as wide as pronotum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broad, slightly wider than width of eyes, produced anteriorly about ¼ of entire median length, lateral margins nearly parallel, disk flat; pronotum slightly longer than crown; mesonotum large, twice as long as pronotum; forewings long, broad, 3 anteapical cells present, outer one closed; clypeus long, very broad, lateral margins broadly convex, median longitudinal carina faint; clypellus about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, apex flared.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,572,1244]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,376,859,884]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view small, triangulate, few short setae on caudoventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1422,860,884]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–100" captionStartId="29.[197,310,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,521,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-497@29.[266,1316,510,1951]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 93–100. Panolidia minuta, sp. nov. (93) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (94) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (95) right style, lateral view; (96) right style, dorsal view; (97) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (98) aedeagus, dorsal view; (99) connective, dorsal view; (100) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long, narrow, few stout setae apically on inner lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1108,1194,896,920]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–100" captionStartId="29.[197,310,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,521,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-497@29.[266,1316,510,1951]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 93–100. Panolidia minuta, sp. nov. (93) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (94) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (95) right style, lateral view; (96) right style, dorsal view; (97) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (98) aedeagus, dorsal view; (99) connective, dorsal view; (100) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
); style long, about as long as aedeagus, apophysis slender (
<figureCitation box="[586,725,932,956]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–100" captionStartId="29.[197,310,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,521,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-497@29.[266,1316,510,1951]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 93–100. Panolidia minuta, sp. nov. (93) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (94) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (95) right style, lateral view; (96) right style, dorsal view; (97) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (98) aedeagus, dorsal view; (99) connective, dorsal view; (100) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs. 95, 96</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, very slender, tubular, apex curved dorsally in lateral view, gonopore subapical on ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[729,865,968,992]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–100" captionStartId="29.[197,310,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,521,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-497@29.[266,1316,510,1951]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 93–100. Panolidia minuta, sp. nov. (93) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (94) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (95) right style, lateral view; (96) right style, dorsal view; (97) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (98) aedeagus, dorsal view; (99) connective, dorsal view; (100) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs. 97, 98</figureCitation>
); connective small, nearly T-shaped, without membrane, stem very short; (
<figureCitation box="[423,507,1004,1028]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–100" captionStartId="29.[197,310,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,521,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-497@29.[266,1316,510,1951]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 93–100. Panolidia minuta, sp. nov. (93) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (94) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (95) right style, lateral view; (96) right style, dorsal view; (97) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (98) aedeagus, dorsal view; (99) connective, dorsal view; (100) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 99</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, narrow (
<figureCitation box="[889,987,1004,1028]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–100" captionStartId="29.[197,310,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[271,1312,521,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-497@29.[266,1316,510,1951]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 93–100. Panolidia minuta, sp. nov. (93) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (94) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (95) right style, lateral view; (96) right style, dorsal view; (97) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (98) aedeagus, dorsal view; (99) connective, dorsal view; (100) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
